<item>
            <title>[ISS-397] Handle databases with errors</title>
                <link>http://jira.perfect.org:8080/browse/ISS-397</link>
                <project id="10007" key="ISS">Issues</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/PerfectExamples/Perfect-Turnstile-PostgreSQL-Demo&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/PerfectExamples/Perfect-Turnstile-PostgreSQL-Demo&lt;/a&gt;&#160;as an example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) If the Postgres database is not set up properly or wrong user&#160;configuration, the demo will always show in bold without error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;proybs-MBP:turnstile swift$ ./.build/release/PerfectTurnstilePostgreSQLDemo&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;INFO&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Running setup: users&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;INFO&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Running setup: tokens&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;INFO&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Starting HTTP server on 0.0.0.0:8181&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should&#160;validate if the hostname, username and password is setup correctly before starting HTTP server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) Attempt to register without Postgres process running will crash Perfect server with:&lt;br/&gt;
Error... Invalid session ID&lt;br/&gt;
Illegal instruction: 4&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should catch no valid connection and return error in JSON &quot;Could not login/register, please try again later&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
